@imsodin

> > concern that the currently-unmaintained gogo protobuf will break when Go 1.19 is released, similarly to how quic-go broke with 1.18;
> 
> What's that concern based on? quic-go is not a good example, it's replicating internal go library code that needs to be adapted on every release, thus the qtls- package. That has nothing to do with gogo-protobuf.

Apologies for the bad example.  Please note in my initial post, "A member of the Debian Go Packaging Team (not aviau) recommended that someone should ask"  The request took place on #debian-golang on OFTC.  I have requested that this colleague follow-up at this issue.
